3. e5
{ Of course! Given a chance, we roar :@@EndBracket@@ After all we are wolves! }
3... Nd5 4. Nc3 { Challenging the Knight on d5 which is quite active. } 4...
Nxc3
{ is an option but in a way doesn't seem to be right as it only helps White to open up the c1 Bishop after dxc3. But in turn we get doubled c-pawns. I don't think the doubled pawns are a hindrance in any way as the d-file is open and it will only benefit us. }
5. dxc3 Nc6
{ Grandmaster Adly Ahmed steered into this direction quite a number of times in his rapid/blitz games, OTB chess @@StartBracket@@Over the board@@EndBracket@@ just to be certain :@@EndBracket@@ , as nowadays it's all online. I even faced this against Adly in the World Rapid in 2019. }
6. Bf4
{ This move seems to be in the spirit of the position, bolstering the central pawn on e5. }
