{ The Accelerated Dragon! Like the Standard Dragon Variation, Black develops the Bishop to g7 in the Accelerated Dragon. But the major difference here is that Black avoids playing ...d7–d6 and can later play ...d7–d5 in one move if possible.   For example, if White tries to play in the style of the Yugoslav Attack with  5.Nc3  Bg7  6.Be3  Nf6  7.f3  O-O  8.Qd2  ,  then  8...d5!  equalizes immediately. So unlike in the normal Dragon, Black delays playing the move ...d6 for as long as possible, prioritizing piece development instead.    The critical test of Black's move order is 5.c4, the Maróczy Bind. White hopes to cramp Black's position by impeding the ...d7–d5 and ...b7–b5 pawn thrusts. Generally, this line is less tactical than many of the other Sicilian variations, and play involves much strategic maneuvering on both sides. }
5. c4
{ The Maroczy Bind! Gaining space immediately. And by the way, I read a very nice book by Andrian Mikhalchishin and Georg Mohr on Understanding Maroczy structures by Thinkers Publishing. It deals with the Maroczy structure arising from various different openings. A beautiful book, I must say, illustrating the typical plans and motifs. Yeah... So let's go ahead now with the opening phase. }
5... Bg7 6. Be3 { Strengthening the Knight on d4. } 6... Nh6
{ A strange way to place the Knight, but Black's main idea is to keep the f-file open for...f5 breaks. }
7. h3
{ Confining the Knight totally by keeping an eye on the g4 square. White intends to play Qd2 next and for that, he should first prevent the Knight from hoping to g4. }
7... O-O 8. Qd2
{ And now we corner the Knight on the rim of the board. The threat is Nxc6 and Bxh6. }
8... Nxd4 9. Bxd4 Bxd4 10. Qxd4
{ It is a huge achievement to have gotten rid of the main Bishop on g7 @@StartBracket@@ The Dragon Bishop @@EndBracket@@ and now White enjoys a healthy advantage. }
10... f5 11. Nc3
{ And Black's position is full of weaknesses. For instance, we can play long castle and march ahead with the h pawn by h4-h5 and exploit the absence of the dark-squared Bishop. }
