4. Nxe4 Nd7
{ This is the mainline of the Rubinstein variation. Black's main idea is to challenge the central Knight on e4 by Ngf6 with the support of the d7 Knight, so that when White exchanges the Knight on f6, Black will retain his second Knight there in that place. And at the top level, this system has been employed heavily by the German Grandmaster Georg Meier, who religiously uses it as his main weapon. }
